Title : David Bevan (cricketer)
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}
{{Use British English|date=February 2016}}
'''David Gordon Bevan''' (born 11 June 1943) is a retired [[cricket]]er who played as a right-handed batsman between 1964 and 1974 for [[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]]. He was also an overseas player for [[Eastern Province cricket team|Eastern Province]] in the 1973/74 season, and played [[minor county cricket]] for [[Suffolk County Cricket Club]] in 1977.<ref name="capro">{{cite web | url=https://cricketarchive.com/Gloucestershire/Players/24/24516/24516.html | title=Player Profile: David Bevan | publisher=Cricket Archive | accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref name="cricpro" />

Bevan, who was born in [[Gloucester]], scored 706 [[first-class cricket|first-class]] runs across his career of 36 matches at a [[batting average (cricket)|batting average]] of 13.21, and 107 runs in [[List-A|one day cricket]] from six games.<ref name="cricpro">{{cite web | url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/9431.html | title=Player Profile: David Bevan | publisher=ESPNcricinfo | accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> 101 of these first-class runs were scored in his three games for Eastern Province.<ref name="FC Batting For Each Team">{{cite web | url=https://cricketarchive.com/Gloucestershire/Players/24/24516/f_Batting_by_Team.html | title=FC Batting For Each Team | publisher=Cricket Archive | accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref> The majority of his cricket was played in 1967, when he made 17 [[County Championship]] appearances for Gloucestershire, the only season when his number of games reached double figures.<ref name="Season By Season FC Batting">{{cite web | url=https://cricketarchive.com/Gloucestershire/Players/24/24516/f_Batting_by_Season.html | title=Season By Season FC Batting | publisher=Cricket Archive | accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>

He joined [[Leinster Cricket Club]] in [[Dublin]] as club professional in 1978,<ref name="Leinster">{{cite web|url=http://www.cricketleinster.ie/news/the-ultimate-professionals|title=The Ultimate Professionals|last=Siggins|first=Ger|date=20 August 2013|publisher=Cricket Leinster|accessdate=5 February 2017}}</ref> playing for the Senior 1s and coaching at all levels.

